column4: @PSK & Co KG: I modiefied the powerline at 341,300 so you can lay your tracks. Enjoy!
could you help with some signals at 200,253?
I don't realise what the problem is. Please explain.
I noticed your track layout of using 2 tracks for increased traffic on the lines and i am trying to do something like it.
however the coal train will not go out of the station
Try to copy Pollingville station at 434,464.
The trick is to build signals before and after the station, not in the station itself.
Of cause you need double tracks before and after the station to get this layout working.
That much is all i know of the signals here. I orginally came from openttd
You should use regular signals wherever it is possible.
I was using long block signals
Avoid using long block signals except in very special (and very rare) situations.
I suggest 1 modification: the bypass in the east should be a bit longer (as long as the longest train on the route).
I would like to know if it could cause any problems
Torwell branch station should work as intended. No train sill ever reach appingby becouse of the one way signal at 56,240.
No train wil ever reach Appingby because of the one way signal at 56,240. Torwell branch station should work as intended.
If you ever need something powered, just let me know. Thanks for the help
